Sequences not divisible by 5 (no digit is 5): $8^n$.
Sequences not divisible by 2 AND not divisible by 5 (digits in $\{1, 3, 7, 9\}$): $4^n$.
Number of good sequences = $9^n - (5^n + 8^n - 4^n)$.
The probability is $1 - (5/9)^n - (8/9)^n + (4/9)^n$.
